## stacklite — skill routing

When the user's request matches an available command, invoke it as your FIRST action.
The command has specialized workflows that produce better results than ad-hoc answers.

Routing rules:
- Product ideas, "is this worth building", brainstorming → `/plan`
- Architecture review, "lock in the plan" → `/eng-review`
- Code review, "check my diff", pre-landing review → `/review`
- Security audit, "check for vulnerabilities" → `/secure`
- Performance review, "check for perf issues" → `/perf`
- Ship, deploy, push, create PR → `/ship`
- Bugs, errors, "why is this broken" → `/investigate`
- Weekly retro, "what did we ship" → `/retro`
- Update docs after shipping → `/doc`
